# Rename to CODEOWNERS and replace the placeholders.
#
# INVARIANT: every path must list AT LEAST TWO owners. GitHub does not count
# self-approval, so once the ruleset's require_code_owner_review is on, a sole
# code owner can never merge their own PRs — the repo deadlocks.
#
# The last matching line wins. Route sensitive paths (CI, agent config, schema,
# the style guide) explicitly even though * already covers them — explicit
# entries survive future * changes.

*                              @SENIOR-1 @SENIOR-2
/.github/                      @SENIOR-1 @SENIOR-2
/CLAUDE.md                     @SENIOR-1 @SENIOR-2
/.claude/                      @SENIOR-1 @SENIOR-2
/docs/style.md                 @SENIOR-1 @SENIOR-2
# Stack-specific sensitive paths — schema, lint/test configs (coverage
# excludes are a suppression vector), infra:
# /backend/prisma/schema.prisma  @SENIOR-1 @SENIOR-2
# /**/eslint.config.js           @SENIOR-1 @SENIOR-2
# /**/vitest.config.*            @SENIOR-1 @SENIOR-2
